title: ICE using `return_position_impl_trait_in_trait` with default implementation

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code [playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=fd65e6bb7ec1ed55d2113ab294523435) rustc panics on: ```rust #![feature(return_position_impl_trait_in_trait)] trait FilterOddsIteratorExt: Iterator + Sized { fn filter_odds(self) -> impl Iterator { self.filter(|i| i % 2 != 0) } } impl FilterOddsIteratorExt for T where T: Iterator {} fn main() { _ = (0..10).filter_odds(); } ``` but not on: ```rust trait FilterOddsIteratorExt: Iterator + Sized { fn filter_odds(self) -> impl Iterator; } impl FilterOddsIteratorExt for T where T: Iterator { fn filter_odds(self) -> impl Iterator { self.filter(|i| i % 2 != 0) } } fn main() { _ = (0..10).filter_odds(); } ``` note that when not using the implementation, the compiler doesn't panic, but gives a `mismatch types` error (try commenting `main`) ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.66.0-nightly (0ca356586 2022-10-06) binary: rustc commit-hash: 0ca356586fed56002b10920fd21ddf6fb12de797 commit-date: 2022-10-06 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.66.0-nightly LLVM version: 15.0.2 ```
